article.headline: Wichita State 64, Illinois State 57
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. (AP) -- Kyle Wilson scored 18 points and Sean Ogirri added 16 as Wichita State beat Illinois State 64-57 to win the Missouri Valley Conference championship. After Illinois State (9-18, 4-14 MVC) rallied to tie the game at 39, Sean Ogirri hit back-to-back 3-pointers as Wichita State (23-7, 14-4) scored nine straight points. Greg Dilliard scored four points as Illinois State got within two, but Kyle Wilson scored eight points in an 11-6 run to seal the win. P.J. Couisnard added 10 points for the Shockers and Ryan Marting had nine points and 13 rebounds. Wichita State won its first outright regular-season conference title since 1983. Levi Dyer led the Redbirds with 17 points, while Roberto Fortes scored 12 and Michael Vandello had 10. Illinois State made 12-of-28 3-point shots.
